# Create a New World

Opening the Meta Horizon Worlds desktop editor takes you to the editorâ€™s **Creation Home**.

![The Creation Home page](data:image/png;base64,)

From this page, you can open an existing world that youâ€™ve created, or start creating a new one.

**To create a new world**

- Open the Worlds desktop editor.

  ![The Start button on the app icon](data:image/png;base64,)
- On the **Creation Home** page, click **New World**.

  ![The New World button](data:image/png;base64,)
- When the desktop editor opens, click **Rename World** from the main menu.

  ![The Rename World option](data:image/png;base64,)
- Provide a name for your new world

  ![Providing a name for your new world](data:image/png;base64,)

  **Note**: If you do not provide a name for your new world, it will still exist and be saved as normal. However, the next time you open it, it will be called â€œNew Worldâ€ with the count of how many worlds youâ€™ve created without names appended to it (for instance, â€œNew World 4.â€ If you do this several times, you may end up with multiple worlds called by similar names, potentially causing confusion. You can always rename it to something else at a later time.
- Click **Save**.
